- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with role discovery in graphs, which is a problem related to network analysis. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an alternating least squares framework with convex constraints, which is a machine learning approach. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with graph analysis, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a supervised approach to role discovery, which is an AI problem. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with multi-relational graphs, which is a database problem.
